.library man.dfs
.synopsis
User validation program.
.syntax
NONAME
R NONAME
.description
NONAME allows the user to change certain validation
parameters on the current system.
These changes are made in the LUD and UFD.

Valid NONAME sub-commands:
.nofill;

LIST USER user
LIST GAN
LIST LUD
CHANGE user
NAMES
HELP
INSTRUCTIONS
QUIT
LIST, CHANGE, NAMES, HELP,
INSTRUCTIONS OR QUIT.

The LIST and CHANGE commands operate on the following data:

1. USER NAME
2. DISTRICT
3. GLOBAL ACCOUNT
UNIVERSAL USER NO.
4. LICENSE (TY or AS)
5. SUPPRESS TYMSHARE MESSAGE AT LOGIN (YES or NO)
6. INIT FILE NAME
7. TIME ZONE
SUBJECT TO DAYLIGHT SAVINGS (YES or NO)
8. DISCONNECT OPTION (DETACH, RUN or LOGOUT)
9. MODE (PDP or XEXEC)
10. QUOTA IN
QUOTA OUT
11. AMOUNT OF CORE
12. GFD ACCESS (YES or NO)
13. PROJECT CODE REQUIRED (YES or NO)
14. RESTRICTED USER BIT (YES or NO)
15. TRU BUDGET
17. ALLOW ATTACH ON LOGIN (YES or NO)
18. FORCE ATTACH ON LOGIN (YES or NO)
19. ALLOW MULTIPLE JOBS (YES or NO)
20. ALLOW USER TO LOGON UNDER THIS NAME (YES or NO)
